8393	\begin{lemma}[The coproduct-of-pullback-fst comparison is an isomorphism]
8394	  \label{lem:isIso_sigmaDesc_fst_mathlib}
8395	  \lean{CategoryTheory.FinitaryPreExtensive.isIso_sigmaDesc_fst}
8396	  \mathlibok
8397	  \textit{Provided by Mathlib.}
8398	  In a finitary pre-extensive category, for a finite index type \(\alpha\) in \(\operatorname{Type}
8399	  0\), a base \(S\), a family \((X_a \to S)_{a \in \alpha}\) and a single \(Y \to S\), the comparison
8400	  map \(\operatorname{Sigma.desc}\) of the pullback first-projections
8401	  \(\coprod_a (X_a \times_S Y) \to (\coprod_a X_a) \times_S Y\) is an isomorphism. This is the
8402	  primitive on which the binary distributivity Lemma~\ref{lem:isIso_sigmaDesc_map_mathlib} and the
8403	  one-sided form Lemma~\ref{lem:prod_coproduct_distrib} rest. \emph{It is stated in Mathlib only for}
8404	  \(\alpha : \operatorname{Type} 0\), which is why the whole distributivity chain
8405	  (Lemma~\ref{lem:coproduct_distrib_fibrePower}) is confined to \(\operatorname{Type} 0\) and the
8406	  cover index is reduced to \(\mathrm{Fin}(n)\) at Lemma~\ref{lem:cech_backbone_left_sigma}.
8407	\end{lemma}
