8421	\begin{lemma}[A wide pullback over a terminal base is the product of its legs]
8422	  \label{lem:widePullbackCone_isLimitOfFan_mathlib}
8423	  \lean{CategoryTheory.Limits.WidePullbackCone.isLimitOfFan}
8424	  \mathlibok
8425	  \textit{Provided by Mathlib.}
8426	  When the base of a wide pullback is a terminal object, a limiting fan of the legs is a limit of
8427	  the wide-pullback diagram. Hence in \(\operatorname{Over} S\) --- where \(\operatorname{Over.mk}
8428	  (\mathrm{id}_S)\) is terminal --- the wide pullback over \(S\) of a family is the product of the
8429	  legs in the slice, which is what lets the fibre power over \(S\) be treated as an iterated
8430	  product in Lemma~\ref{lem:coproduct_distrib_fibrePower}.
8431	\end{lemma}
